      <p>The clean line to keep in mind: Intuit&rsquo;s payroll service is what processes direct deposit &mdash; it debits the company account, holds nothing of ours, and releases funds to employees on its own schedule, which we can&rsquo;t accelerate or guarantee. Everything <em>around</em> that is the operational accounting work an independent firm does: verifying the company bank account, getting employee bank details and authorizations on file correctly, configuring the payroll schedule so runs are approved before each cutoff, and reconciling payroll wages, taxes, and the net direct-deposit debit against the bank statement every period. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written scope. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s payroll service; an Intuit account, subscription, billing, or held-transfer matter stays with Intuit.</p>
